full_text: @Kim_Scott_15 I have my Smartboard frozen when I take away points from a student and they can only hear the sound. I don't point it out to the class.

full_text: @Kim_Scott_15 Student buy in to Dojo is key especially with older students. One thing I do that helps a lot is only awarding positive points visibly.
full_text(utf-8): b'@Kim_Scott_15 Student buy in to Dojo is key especially with older students. One thing I do that helps a lot is only awarding positive points visibly.'

full_text: @Kim_Scott_15 My students 6th and 7th this past year liked exchanging points for mini notebooks, pens, flavored lip gloss, candy all from dollar store.

full_text: @Kim_Scott_15 The biggest tip I have is giving students a voice in how Dojo will operate. Do they want whole class rewards, individual, prizes?
